---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout title="Olle Rönn | CV">
  <section class="hero cv-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">CV</p>

    <h1>CV</h1>

    <p class="lead">
      IT engineering student specializing in digital infrastructure and cybersecurity.
      I have practical experience in Identity & Access Management, Active Directory,
      Entra ID, Azure and PowerShell automation, along with a strong foundation in
      networking, Linux, security and technical documentation.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Experience</p>
      <h2>Relevant experience</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="experience-list">
      <article class="card experience-card">
        <div class="experience-meta">
          <span class="tag">Nov 2025 – Jan 2026</span>
          <p>Gothenburg</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3>Stena Group IT</h3>
          <p class="role">Identity & Access Management</p>

          <p>
            Worked with IAM in a larger enterprise IT environment, supporting user,
            permission and privileged account management across Active Directory,
            Entra ID and Azure.
          </p>

          <ul>
            <li>Performed access reviews and account analysis.</li>
            <li>Analyzed security risks and attack methods in a real IT environment.</li>
            <li>Used PowerShell for data collection, automation and process support.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Education</p>
      <h2>Education</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="grid">
      <article class="card">
        <span class="tag">Planned start Aug 2026</span>
        <h3>Chalmers University of Technology</h3>
        <p class="role">MSc in High-Performance Computer Systems, 120 credits</p>
        <p>
          Planned master's studies focused on high-performance computer systems,
          parallel programming, computer architecture and distributed systems.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <span class="tag">Aug 2023 - Jun 2026</span>
        <h3>University of Borås</h3>
        <p class="role">BSc in IT Engineering - Digital Infrastructure and Cybersecurity, 180 credits</p>
        <p>
          Three-year engineering programme focused on digital infrastructure,
          networking, systems, cloud technologies and cybersecurity.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <span class="tag">Aug 2019 - Jun 2022</span>
        <h3>Lindholmens Tekniska Gymnasium</h3>
        <p>
          Upper secondary education in information and media with a focus on design,
          programming and computer technology.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Technical skills</p>
      <h2>Technical skills</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="skills-grid">
      <article class="card">
        <h3>IT Infrastructure & Networking</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Windows environments and basic system administration</li>
          <li>TCP/IP, routing and switching at CCNA level</li>
          <li>Network fundamentals and troubleshooting</li>
          <li>Linux server basics and SSH administration</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>Identity & Access Management</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Active Directory, Entra ID and Azure</li>
          <li>User accounts, permissions and privileged accounts</li>
          <li>Access reviews and account analysis</li>
          <li>IAM processes in an enterprise IT environment</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>Cybersecurity</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Security fundamentals and analysis of attack methods</li>
          <li>Network traffic analysis with Wireshark and PCAP files</li>
          <li>Basic security monitoring and incident response concepts</li>
          <li>Server hardening with SSH keys, UFW and fail2ban</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>Scripting & Automation</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>PowerShell for administration, automation and data collection</li>
          <li>Basic Python programming</li>
          <li>Basic SQL</li>
          <li>Git and GitHub-based documentation workflows</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>Tools & Technologies</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Azure and basic cloud services</li>
          <li>Docker and Docker Compose</li>
          <li>Portainer, Uptime Kuma, Homepage and Nginx</li>
          <li>Wireshark, Kali Linux and CyberChef</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>Standards & Frameworks</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Basic understanding of NIS2</li>
          <li>Basic understanding of ISO/IEC 27001</li>
          <li>Risk awareness and security documentation</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Certifications & courses</p>
      <h2>Certifications and relevant courses</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="cv-two-column">
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Certifications</h3>

        <ul>
          <li>Cisco IT Essentials</li>
          <li>Cisco Introduction to Cybersecurity</li>
          <li>Cisco Cybersecurity Essentials</li>
          <li>Cisco CCNA: ITN, SRWE and ENSA</li>
          <li>Cisco Ethical Hacker</li>
          <li>Cisco CyberOps Associate</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>Relevant courses</h3>

        <p>
          Networking, operating systems, server systems and infrastructure,
          databases and data analysis, IoT and cloud services, cybersecurity for
          connected devices, Python programming, project management, technical
          reporting, tactical cybersecurity and incident response.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Projects</p>
      <h2>Selected technical projects</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="cv-two-column">
      <article class="card">
        <span class="tag">Version 1 Complete</span>
        <h3>Secure Homelab</h3>
        <p>
          Built, secured and documented a Linux-based homelab using Ubuntu Server,
          SSH key authentication, UFW, fail2ban, Docker, Portainer, Uptime Kuma,
          Homepage and Nginx.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <span class="tag">Live</span>
        <h3>Portfolio Website</h3>
        <p>
          Built this personal portfolio with Astro, GitHub and Vercel to present
          technical projects, CV information and documented learning.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>

    <div class="section-link">
    <a href="/projects">View all projects</a>
  </div>

  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Additional experience</p>
      <h2>Additional work experience</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="grid">
      <article class="card">
        <span class="tag">Sep 2024 - Present</span>
        <h3>OnePartnerGroup</h3>
        <p>
          Warehouse work including forklift operation, goods handling and preparation
          of deliveries.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <span class="tag">Apr 2023 - Present</span>
        <h3>City of Gothenburg</h3>
        <p>
          Support role working with youth in structured daily activities, including
          digital engagement and practical support.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <span class="tag">May 2022 - Jun 2023</span>
        <h3>Bauhaus</h3>
        <p>
          Sales role within construction and plumbing, combined with goods handling
          using forklift and lifting equipment.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Languages & licences</p>
      <h2>Languages and licences</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="cv-two-column">
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Languages</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Swedish - native</li>
          <li>English - fluent, spoken and written</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>Licences</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Swedish driving licence, category B</li>
          <li>Forklift licence A1–A4, B1–B3</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  .cv-hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 5.2vw, 4.2rem);
  }

  .experience-list {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .experience-card {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 220px 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .experience-meta p {
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  .role {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: -0.25rem;
  }

  .skills-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .cv-two-column {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  ul {
    margin: 0.75rem 0 0;
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
    color: var(--text-soft);
  }

  li {
    margin-bottom: 0.45rem;
  }

  li::marker {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .section-link {
  margin-top: 1.25rem;
}

.section-link a {
  color: var(--accent);
  font-weight: 750;
}

.section-link a:hover {
  color: var(--text);
}

  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .experience-card {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 0.75rem;
    }

    .skills-grid,
    .cv-two-column {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>